unittitle_ssm: International Federation of Professional and Technical Engineers, Local 66 Records
abstract_ssm:
The International Federation of Professional and Technical Engineers (IFTPE), Local 66 is a labor union for engineers in the New York City and New Jersey area.  During its long history, Local 66 organized architects, draftsmen and surveyors, as well as chemical, civil, electrical, mechanical, and industrial engineers.

The collection covers the history of IFTPE, Local 66 in its efforts to organize and represent engineers in the New York City and New Jersey area.  The bulk of the collection consists of shop files documenting Local 66's successful and unsuccessful organization and bargaining efforts.

unittitle_ssm: Port Authority: Labor Relations Instructions. Promulgated by the PA in 1970, the LRI provided for an unilateral panel to hear labor disputes. Internal hearings held by the PA Commission heard the objections of the several PA unions. Further objections were taken to the state level (including the Public Employment Relations Board; State senate bills 8810 and 8973 in 1972). In 1976, an "independent" panel (the PA Employment Relations Board) was established by law to replace the LRI panel. Records include documents of the internal and state hearings, bills, correspondence from the unions, drafts of the proposed labor instructions, procedures for representation, precedents, testimonies by Local 66, AFL-CIO legislative pamphlets, Joint Gubernatorial Committee reports, resumes for selection of panelists for the new PA Employment Relations Board.
